Dolly: Now, I like to think I'm an open-minded person, so I almost want to say I wouldn't write anything off completely. 
Dolly: BUT... if I think about it more, I'd say that I wouldn't want to wear business attire ever again.
Dolly: I can say that because I've done it, I tried it! And I know hate it! 
Dolly: I used to work as the Senior Commercial Manager of National Strategic Acquisitions – 
Dolly: Don't ask what that all entails even I couldn't tell you. 
Dolly: Anyways, I was really trying to prove myself there, when I started, I was the only woman in that office, and a lesbian so you can imagine how that would go at times.
Dolly:I really dressed the part so they would take me seriously, like a suit (hah!) of armour. 
Dolly: Pant suits, loafers, collars, the whole shebang. 
Dolly: Well, never again! 
// (reveals dislikes business, retired)
