Dolly: Ah that's easy. 
Dolly: I met my wife Leanne at a concert back in the 80s. We were seeing The Matchmakers - really cool local punk band that we both loved. 
Dolly: Anyways, we met at the merch table both trying to buy the last T-shirt. 
Dolly: We bickered for a little bit, Leanne said I cut the line, and to be honest with you I did, but don't tell her I admitted that. 
Dolly: Anyways, the poor girl at the merch table didn't know what to do. 
Dolly: Finally, I offered to buy her a CD if she would let me have it. 
Dolly: She agreed, we spent the entire concert hanging out, and the rest is history! 
Dolly: The shirt is actually a bit simple for me, so I used to wear it with some of my flashy skirts and my favourite heels! 
Dolly: Of course, I still have that shirt and now it really belongs to the both of us. I love it! 
//(reveals likes flashy, heels, skirts dislikes simple)
