Dolly: I mean, there's lots. You get to be as old as me and you've worn an outfit or two that you regret. 
Dolly: But the worst one, the specific one that comes to mind, is what I wore to my job interview for Corp Ltd.
Dolly: I was applying to be a receptionist, and I wanted them to take me seriously, 
Dolly: So I wore this awful, modest business suit. It had a turtleneck in these dull, muted brown colors, and it was uncomfortable as hell.
Dolly: I don't mind an uncomfy outfit if it looks good – I still love heels after all! – but this outfit didn't even look nice. I think my mom picked it out for me. 
Dolly: I look back now and can't believe I dressed like that for over 40 years!
//  (reveals dislikes muted, modest, likes heels)
